<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="507" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1400,2039]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1472,1498]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wang, 2003)" baseAuthorityName="Wang" baseAuthorityYear="2003" box="[658,1014,1472,1498]" class="Insecta" family="Cosmopterigidae" genus="Meleonoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jigongshanica">
<emphasis box="[658,854,1472,1498]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">M. jigongshanica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Wang, S. X." box="[868,1006,1472,1498]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" pagination="195 - 213" refId="ref14825" refString="Wang, S. X. (2003) A study of Cryptolechia Zeller (Lepidoptera: Oecophoridae) in China (I), with descriptions of fifteen new species. Entomologia Sinica, 10 (3), 195 - 213. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1744 - 7917.2003. tb 00384. x" type="journal article" year="2003">Wang, 2003</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in the male genitalia. It can be distinguished by the costa with a process medially, the stout juxta and the aedeagus without a row of tiny teeth along the distal half. In 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wang" baseAuthorityYear="2003" box="[308,504,1544,1570]" class="Insecta" family="Cosmopterigidae" genus="Meleonoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jigongshanica">
<emphasis box="[308,504,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">M. jigongshanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the costa lacks a process medially, the juxta is slender and the aedeagus has a row of tiny teeth along the distal half (
<bibRefCitation author="Wang, S. X." box="[529,719,1580,1606]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" pagination="195 - 213" refId="ref14825" refString="Wang, S. X. (2003) A study of Cryptolechia Zeller (Lepidoptera: Oecophoridae) in China (I), with descriptions of fifteen new species. Entomologia Sinica, 10 (3), 195 - 213. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1744 - 7917.2003. tb 00384. x" type="journal article" year="2003">Wang 2003: 207</bibRefCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[730,812,1580,1606]" captionStart="FIGURES 16−21" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1886,1910]" captionTargetBox="[171,1422,196,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-19@13.[160,1428,181,1862]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 16−21. Male genitalia of Meleonoma spp. 16, M. aculeolata sp. nov., holotype, slide No. ZXJ19527; 17, M. rectivalva sp. nov., holotype, slide No. ZXJ19511; 18, M. robustijuxta sp. nov., holotype, slide No. ZXJ19449; 19, M. varilobata sp. nov., holotype, slide No. ZXJ19451; 20, M. basitriangula sp. nov., paratype, ZXJ19590; 21, M. biprocessa sp. nov., holotype, slide No. ZXJ19369. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5832808" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5832808/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="508" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1400,2039]" box="[199,819,1616,1643]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1616,1642]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Description.</emphasis>
Adult (
<figureCitation box="[431,499,1616,1643]" captionStart="FIGURES 4−9" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1266,1290]" captionTargetBox="[185,1402,188,1234]" captionTargetId="figure-24@4.[174,1414,181,1241]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 4−9. Adults of Meleonoma spp. 4, M. aculeolata sp. nov.; 5, M. rectivalva sp. nov.; 6, M. robustijuxta sp. nov.; 7, M. varilobata sp. nov.; 8, M. basitriangula sp. nov.; 9, M. biprocessa sp. nov. All holotypes and males. Scale bars = 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5832802" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5832802/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Forewing length 10.0 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1400,2039]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">
<emphasis box="[199,260,1652,1678]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Head</emphasis>
with vertex blackish brown, frons yellow. Labial palpus with first palpomere blackish brown on outer surface, yellow on inner surface; second palpomere blackish brown except yellow on basal 3/5 of inner surface; third palpomere yellow, slender, approx. 1/2 length of second palpomere. Antenna blackish brown on dorsal surface; scape yellow, flagellum blackish brown alternated with yellow on ventral surface.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1400,2039]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">
<emphasis box="[199,280,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Thorax</emphasis>
and tegula blackish brown. Forewing blackish brown, with ill-defined discal, discocellular and plical dots; fringe greyish brown. Hindwing and fringe greyish brown. Legs yellow; on ventral surface, fore- and midlegs blackish brown except tarsi yellow at apex of each tarsomere, hind femur and tibia with blackish-brown scales, hind tarsus blackish brown except yellow at apex of each tarsomere.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1400,2039]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1437,151,573]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="508" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">
<emphasis box="[199,366,1940,1966]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[382,468,1940,1966]" captionStart="FIGURES 16−21" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1886,1910]" captionTargetBox="[171,1422,196,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-19@13.[160,1428,181,1862]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 16−21. Male genitalia of Meleonoma spp. 16, M. aculeolata sp. nov., holotype, slide No. ZXJ19527; 17, M. rectivalva sp. nov., holotype, slide No. ZXJ19511; 18, M. robustijuxta sp. nov., holotype, slide No. ZXJ19449; 19, M. varilobata sp. nov., holotype, slide No. ZXJ19451; 20, M. basitriangula sp. nov., paratype, ZXJ19590; 21, M. biprocessa sp. nov., holotype, slide No. ZXJ19369. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5832808" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5832808/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
). Uncus wide at base, gradually narrowed to basal 3/4, distal 1/4 abruptly narrowed, forming a small, heavily sclerotized rectangular process; lateral margin sclerotized from distal 1/3 to apex. Tegumen uniformly wide medially; lateral arm narrowed to rounded apex. Valva narrowed at base, widened medially, distal 1/4 distinctly narrow, thumb-shaped; ventral margin roundly convex medially, with dense setae running from basal 1/4 to apex; costa banded, heavily sclerotized, reaching tip of costal margin, with a large median process asymmetrical in shape: process of left valva longer, narrowed from base to pointed apex, process of right valva stout, rounded at apex. Sacculus wide at base, slightly narrowed to apex; apex straight, dorsoapically produced to a conical process extending upward to basal 1/4 of valva. Saccus nearly as long as uncus, rounded at apex. Juxta indistinctly joined by membrane anteriorly; lateral arm stout, sub-rectangular, slightly widened to obtuse apex, heavily sclerotized. Aedeagus longer than valva, basal 4/7 more sclerotized, distal 3/7 membranous; slender, heavily sclerotized band running from basal 4/7 to apex, with a small sub-rectangular process near apex, with a few denticles in vesica apically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,573]" box="[199,401,439,465]" pageId="7" pageNumber="508">Female unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
